revision.text:
The '''1st Division''' ({{lang-no|1. divisjon}}) is a former unit in the [[Norwegian Army]], responsible for the defence of [[Eastern Norway]] along with [[2nd Division (Norway)|2nd Division]].

Following the [[Operation Weserübung|German invasion of Norway]] in 1940 the Norwegian 1st Division, commanded by [[Major General]] [[Carl Johan Erichsen]], was responsible for defending the land areas on both side of the [[Oslofjord]] against the invading troops. The division was not well prepared for the situation, the troops were not mobilized and the division's stores depots in [[Fredrikstad]] were captured by the Germans already on 9 April. The 1st Division was responsible for Fossum Fortress (Høytorp Fort and Trøgstad Fort) in [[Askim]] and the Greåker Fort in [[Sarpsborg]]. The Germans started attacking on 12 April, and there were battles at bridges crossing [[Glomma]] ([[Fossum Bridge]], Langenes Railway Bridge, and a bridge near [[Kykkelsrud Hydroelectric Power Station|Kykkelsrud Power Station]]). Fossum Fortress was surrendered on 13 April. On 14 April a large number of troops in [[Østfold]], around 3,000 men, chose to cross the border to Sweden instead of continuing the fight or surrendering to the German troops. At [[Kongsberg]] two bataillons surrendered without fighting, while some officers and soldiers disagreed with the surrender and defended the [[Battle of Vinjesvingen|Vinje district]] for about one  month.<ref>{{cite book|title=Krigen i Norge 1940. Operasjonene i Østfold |first=Wilhelm |last=Faye |authorlink=Wilhelm Faye |year=1963 |publisher=Forsvarets Krigshistoriske Avdeling / Gyldendal |language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Krig og okkupasjon 1939–1945 |page=54 |first=Magne |last=Skodvin |authorlink=Magne Skodvin |year=1990 |publisher=Samlaget |language=Norwegian |isbn=82-521-3490-4}}</ref><ref name=u45>{{cite book|last=Nordlie |first=J.H |authorlink=Jens Henrik Nordlie |title=Innstilling fra [[Undersøkelseskommisjonen av 1945]]. Bilag  |volume=1 |year=1947 |location=Oslo |publisher=Aschehoug / [[Parliament of Norway]] |language=Norwegian|chapter=Kort oversikt over kampene i Norge våren 1940|pages=107–108 }}</ref>

