'''Bodegas Alejandro Fernández''' is a [[Spanish wine]] company consisting of four wineries (''bodegas''). Alejandro Fernandez first founded  Pesquera Bodega in [[Ribera del Duero]] in 1972. Ribera del Duero was listed at ''[[denominación de origen]]'' status in 1982 largely as a result of his efforts to practice quality winemaking in the region,<ref>[https://www.bbr.com/producer-3412-bodegas-alejandro-fernandez Bodegas Alejandro Fernández] [[Berry Bros. & Rudd]], 3 [[St James's Street]], [[London]]</ref> which was traditionally planted to sugarbeet  and grain.

The vines are planted to low espalier [[Trellis (architecture)|trellis]]es to absorb more heat from the ground, and grow in poor, well-drained soils composed of sand and [[gravel]] above a [[limestone]] and [[clay]] [[subsoil]].<ref>{{official|http://www.grupopesquera.com/index.php/en/bodegas/tinto-pesquera}}</ref>

