With ''[[perestroika]]'' in force, the Moldovan nationalism came in place with the [[Popular Front of Moldova]] being involved. On 27 April 1990, the new flag of the Moldavian SSR consisted of the [[flag of Romania|Romanian tricolor]] with the [[Emblem of the Moldavian Soviet Socialist Republic|emblem of the Moldavian SSR]] in the centre. However, it was decided to use the flag without the emblem until new symbols were worked on. When Moldavia declared sovereignty in June 1990, the new flag was adopted on 6 November 1990 and remains the [[flag of Moldova|flag]] of [[Moldova]] to this day.

