[[File:Karolin arriving in Tallinn 6 May 2013.JPG|thumb|240px|''Karolin'' arriving at Tallinn's Linnahall terminal in 2013.]] '''Linda Line''' was the brand name of ''Lindaliini AS'', an [[Estonia]]n [[ferry]] company operating between [[Tallinn]], Estonia and [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. Its high-speed passenger ferry ''Karolin'' was the fastest vessel sailing between the two cities, linking Tallinn's [[Linnahall]] terminal and Helsinki's Makasiini terminal in 100 minutes. The company was founded in 1997.<ref name=linda>[http://en.lindaline.ee/ Lindaline.ee]</ref> Linda Line had a policy of cancelling departures when wind speeds exceeded 15 metres per second and/or wave heights were over 3 metres.<ref>[http://news.err.ee/616431/bad-weather-disrupts-some-ferry-services-on-monday ERR News. ''Bad weather disrupts some ferry services on Monday.'']</ref>
''Karolin'' was a [[catamaran]] built in [[Australia]] in 2000, which went into service with Linda Line in 2009. She had a capacity of 353 passengers and a maximum speed of 37 knots.<ref name=linda /><ref>[http://www.faktaomfartyg.se/caraibe_jet_2000.htm Faktaomfartyg.se] (Swedish)</ref>
Linda Line ceased operations in November 2017 and filed for bankruptcy in May 2018.<ref>[https://news.err.ee/834522/linda-line-declared-bankrupt-by-court ERR News. ''Linda Line declared bankrupt by court.'']</ref>
