The '''Social Democratic Party''' ({{lang-pt|Partido Social Democrático}}, PSD) is a [[political party]] in [[Cape Verde]].
==History== The PSD was established by João Alem in 1992 as a split from the [[Democratic and Independent Cape Verdean Union]] (UCID).<ref name=HDCV>Richard A Lobban Jr & Paul Khalil Saucier (2007) ''Historical Dictionary of the Republic of Cape Verde'', Scarecrow Press, p181</ref> In the [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 1995|1995 parliamentary elections]] it received only 1,030 votes (0.7%), failing to win a seat.<ref name=AED/>
The [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2001|2001 elections]] saw the party receive just 620 votes (0.5%). Its vote share fell to 0.4% in the [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2006|2006 elections]] and 0.2% in the [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2011|2011 elections]].<ref name=AED>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cv.html Elections in Cape Verde] African Elections Database</ref>
